comments:
That part which until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Waltham Holy Cross. See also Table 2, note (j).

Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London borough of Enfield. 
    See also Table 2, note (p).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Enfield in East Barnet Valley 
    Urban District was transferred from Middlesex to Hertfordshire; in 1894 this 
    area became part of the parish of Monken Hadley, so that thereafter Enfield 
    was again entirely in Middlesex. Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London 
    borough of Enfield. See also Table 2, notes (b), (c), (i) and (p).

That part which until 1.4.1937 formed part of the parish of 
    Hornsey See also Table 2, note (n).

That part which until 1.4.1934 formed parts of the parish of 
    Southgate and Wood Green. See also Table 2, note (n).

That part which until 1.4.1937 formed part of the parish of 
    Hornsey. See also Table 2, note (n).

Created 26.3.1896 from the part of the parish of Hornsey in South 
    Hornsey Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1900 and divided between the parishes of 
    Stoke Newington and Islington. See also Table 2, notes (d) and (f).

That part which until 1.4.1924 formed part of the parish of Enfield. 
    See also Table 2, note (i).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Edmonton in Southgate 
    Urban District. See also Table 2, notes (n) and (o).

Abolished 1.4.1965 and added to the London borough of Haringey. 
    See also Table 2, notes (h), (g) and (q).

Created 1894 out of the part of the parish of Tottenham in Wood 
    Green Urban District. See also Table 2, notes (n) and (o).
